text: Flines-lez-Raches (also Flines-lez-RÃ¢ches) is a commune as well as a village in the Department of Nord, in the Hauts-de-France region. Its churchyard is in the center of the commune. It has an oceanic climate as the result of it being 18 meters above sea level. The average precipitation in every year is about 30 inches, or 753 millimeters. In 2021, the average was 1.25 inches of precipitation. == Other websites == http://www.mairie-flineslesraches.com/ == References == Category:Communes in Nord
